RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 84. Maiden Claiming Purse 54000. (UP TO $9,396 NYSBFOA) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $75,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void)(If No Three Year Olds Are Entered, Starting We ight Shall Be 122 lbs).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POWER IN NUMBERS went to the front, set the pace under pressure from the runner-up to the outside, was asked along the rail on the turn, came under a left-handed crop in upper stretch, responded gamely while fending off the runner-up into the final sixteenth and determinedly prevailed under a strong hand-ride in the shadow of the wire. CLOUD FOREST moved out early then pressed the pace on the outside of the winner, was asked in the three path on the turn while opening up in unison on the rest of the field, came under a right-handed crop while tussling outside the winner in upper stretch, switched to a left-handed crop nearing the furlong marker, continued to fight into the final sixteenth then switched back to a right-handed crop and missed while well clear for the place. PIONEERING SPIRIT was bumped hard at the start, dropped well behind early then angled in outside the five-eighths pole, saved ground under urging around the turn, came out four wide into the stretch and safely secured the show while no threat to the top two. PREDICTED was bumped in the hindquarters at the start, chased the pace on the outside, dropped back late on the backstretch, went around the turn in the four path, dropped to the three path into the stretch and capitulated. GOLDEN PURCHASE broke out and bumped hard with a foe, was urged along on the outside, went five wide around the turn and failed to respond.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOLDIENESS coaxed from the gate, chased three then two wide coming under coaxing at the three-eighths, spun two to three wide for home inhaling the top pair straightened away and drew clear under a drive to prevail. JOEYBIGNOSE five paths off the inside down the backstretch, tucked three wide through the turn coming under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, swung four wide for home and offered up a mild kick. JOEY THE FISH devoid of any speed in the early going, grew detached at the tail of the field five paths off the inside, tucked three then two wide through the turn, swung three to four wide for home and kicked on belatedly to secure the show honors well clear of the rest. WILL BE FAMOUS prompted the leader from the outside four then three wide advancing on that foe into the turn to duel while widening away as a pair from the rest, took over command at the five-sixteenths, took the inside route into upper stretch forcing the backing away PRETTY MISS KEENS to steady now in behind her when overhauled by the top one and tired to the finish. AUDIT COMMITTEE hustled from the gate, chased along the inside under a ride from the seven-sixteenths, spun three wide for home, tired. PRETTY MISS KEENS coaxed from the start, showed the way just off the inside under pressure from WILL BE FAMOUS to the outside, had that rival advance into the turn and dueled with that foe widening from the rest, yielded the front at the five-sixteenths, faded and cut the corner into upper stretch steadying off the heels now of WILL BE FAMOUS as that foe tucked in front straightened away and folded.

WELCOMETOMYWORLD settled just off the pace on the outside, chased in the four path around the turn, pursued the winner in the stretch and was clearly second best. RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 28000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since October 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be V oid)(If No Three Year Olds Are Entered, Starting Weight Shall Be 122 lbs).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BOURBON'S HOPE hustled from the gate, raced six paths off the inside down the backstretch before advancing to vie five then four wide into the turn, tucked three wide midway, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, continued three wide into upper stretch, took over command with three-sixteenths to go outside a pair, dug in gamely to fend off those rivals to the finish. STAR ATTITUDE coaxed from the start, raced forwardly placed just off SOUTHERN PASSAGE in the early stages before knocking heads with that rival briefly, then vied inside a quartet into the turn, had a pair get shaken off a bit when GINNSU WARRIOR tucked inwards from the outside and got placed to coaxing at that station, continued in the inside route into upper stretch and was headed for the front with three-sixteenths to go, fought on inside to preserve the place honors. GINNSU WARRIOR coaxed from the gate, raced five wide in aim of the front before advancing to vie four then three wide into the turn, tucked to the two path near the three-eighths placing VIVE BIEN and SOUTHERN PASSAGE in tight and forcing that pair of rivals to pause briefly, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths, spun just off the inside into upper stretch, dug in between foes and ran on to be along clear for the show honors. RAW COURAGE chased just off the inside at the tail of the field, the lone member not to engage in a pace dispute with nine-sixteenths to go, tipped out to the four path steadily at the midway point on the turn placed to coaxing, angled five wide into upper stretch and weakened in the late stages. VIVE BIEN coaxed from the start, raced four wide down the backstretch before briefly vying four then three wide into the turn, had GINNSU WARRIOR tuck inwards an paused briefly at the three-eighths, swung three to four wide for home and weakened in the stretch. SOUTHERN PASSAGE coaxed from the gate, led early on before briefly knocking heads with STAR ATTITUDE, then vied three then two wide pausing at the three-eighths when put in tight inside of VIVE BIEN due to pressure from GUNNSU WARRIOR, faded and spun just off the inside into upper stretch, then tired through to the finish.

FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 TWICE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR OPTIONAL CLAIMING PRICE OF $45,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 122 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Other Than Claiming Or Starter At A Mile Or Over Since October 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $45,000 (Allowance Horses Preferred) (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void)(If No Three Year Olds Are Entered, Starting Weight Shall Be 122 lbs).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BUSTIN BAY lunged at the start and was off slow, spotted the front two to three lengths, moved up to track the pace on the outside, ranged up in the three path around the turn, was given her cue outside the five-sixteenths, had her hindquarters make contact with FREDDYMO FACTOR while taking the lead in the five path coming to the three-sixteenths then was turned in, drifted in while moving clear shortly thereafter, responded well under a left-handed crop in the final furlong and just held. MIA BEA STAR moved out at the rear then settled on the outside, was urged three wide around the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive, gained fast in the final furlong and finished well to just miss while up for the place. AMITY ISLAND was hustled from the gate then taken under light restraint, came back under urging before the five-eighths pole, moved from the two path to the three path early on the turn, shifted four wide later on that bend, was driven five wide into the stretch, chased outside into the final furlong, gained into the final sixteenth, swapped back to her inside lead late and finished willingly but missed the place while well clear for the show. FREDDYMO FACTOR attended the pace on the outside while in hand, took a short lead late on the backstretch, vied in the two path around the turn, floated four wide into upper stretch, bumped with the hindquarters of the winner while losing the advantage near the three-sixteenths and was taken up then weakened. CURLY GIRL had the rider fall back in the saddle some while taken under a tight hold near the seven-eighths pole, showed the way with company while in hand, lost the advantage late on the backstretch, vied inside under urging on the turn and tired. CARAMOCHA was taken in hand early, dropped back near the five-eighths, saved ground around the turn and was no factor. FOLLOWING THE RACE, THE RIDER OF FREDDYMO FACTOR CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST BUSTIN BAY ALLEGING INTERFERENCE IN UPPER STRETCH. AFTER THE STEWARDS' REVIEW, NO CHANGE WAS MADE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH

RACE.FOOTNOTES: INSPEIGHTOFTRAINER coaxed from the gate, chased just off the inside from near the rear of the compact field, tipped out three wide nudging his way to a clear path at the expense of INCANTATION just outside the three-eighths marker, came under coaxing near the quarter pole and went three wide into upper stretch getting brushed by GOING IN STYLE straightened away, rallied to issue a challenge through the final furlong seizing narrow command just inside the sixteenth pole, then dug in gamely to prevail on the wire. WINNING CONNECTION chased along the inside from near the rear of the field, came under coaxing at the three-eighths, advanced through the latter portion of the turn to take command inside a trio cutting the corner into upper stretch, dug in under lone threat through the final furlong and was collared just inside the sixteenth marker, fought on gamely to the finish. KINGFISH STEVENS chased four then five wide coming under coaxing near the quarter pole, swung four wide into upper stretch, kept on to secure the show honors. GOING IN STYLE coaxed from the start, showed the way in hand just off the inside, came under coaxing at the five-sixteenths under threat from a trio, yielded the front and spun just off the inside into upper stretch floating out briefly to brush with INSPEIGHTOFTRAINER, then weakened through to the finish. INCANTATION three wide in pursuit, came under coaxing at the seven-sixteenths, got nudged four wide near the three-eighths pole by INSPEIGHTOFTRAINER looking for a clear path from in behind the leader, faded through the latter portion of the turn under a drive, went four wide for home, folded and was eased home to the wire.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Top Flight S. AQUEDUCT RACE 7 1 1/8M Dirt CR: 102. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Non-Lasix Race pursuant to 4043.2 (7)(e)(5) Lasix not permitted within 48 hours of post time. By subscription of $100 each which should accompany the nominations; $500 to pass the entry box and an additiona l $500 to start. For horses not originally nominated, a supplemental nomination payment of $500 in addition to the entry and starting fees may be made at any time prior to the closing of entries. The purse to be divided 55% to the owner of the winner, 20% to second, 12% to third, 6% to fourth, 4% to fifth and 3% divided equally amongst the remaining finishers. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners of a Graded Sweepstake at a mile or over since September 1, 2022 allowed 3 lbs.; of a Graded Sweepstake at a mile or o ver in 2022 or a sweepstake at a mile or over other than State-Bred since November 1, 2022 allowed 5 lbs. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Closed Saturday, March 18, 2023 with 13 Original Nominations and 1 Supplement.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FALCONET was hustled from the gate, shifted from the rail to the three path early on the first turn, tracked the leader on the outside, moved closer in the three path around the far turn, made a bid while asked at the five-sixteenths, turned into upper stretch on even terms for the lead, fought outside of TIMELESS JOURNEY under the crop to near the sixteenth-pole then moved clear under good handling. KATHLEEN O. was off a step slow then urged some early, rounded the first turn in the two path, settled at the rear, passed the nine-sixteenths under a strong hand-ride, went four then five wide around the far turn, chased outside in the stretch, gained gradually late and got up for the place while no threat to the winner. TIMELESS JOURNEY dropped back nearing the first turn, moved from the two path to the rail early on that bend, was well placed just off the pace, drafted near the rail on the far turn, was given her cue with a clear opening at the five-sixteenths, gained to make a bid then took a short lead outside the quarter-pole, fought with the winner under a drive until near the sixteenth-pole then weakened and lost the place but was clear for the show. LET HER INSPIRE U went three then four wide around the first turn, settled on the outside, was roused four wide on the final turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive and lacked the needed response. MOMMASGOTTARUN went to the front, showed the way in the two path, was asked under threat at the five-sixteenths, lost the advantage outside the quarter-pole and gave way.
